Sentencas: Trace impurities in coal-derived syngas pose a threat on the performance and durability of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) operated in syngas.

Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural analysis of nickel-yttria-stabilized zirconia electrode operated in phosphorus-containing syngas

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance analysis shows that both the charge transfer resistance and the diffusion resistance increase with time during exposure to the P-containing syngas.
Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural analysis of nickel-yttria-stabilized zirconia electrode operated in phosphorus-containing syngas

Sentencas: The diffusion resistance increases faster than the charge transfer resistance.

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction (XRD) and X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS) studies show that phosphorus is incorporated into the Ni-YSZ electrode, leading to the formation of secondary phases of nickel phosphate and zirconium phosphate.
Titulo: Electrochemical and microstructural analysis of nickel-yttria-stabilized zirconia electrode operated in phosphorus-containing syngas

Sentencas: The incorporation of phosphorus into the anode is accelerated by an applied electric field.
